verbose_text: By day 12, F5/LDeltaP T cells had fallen in number and were not significantly different from F5/B6 cells (XREF_FIG D), suggesting that expression of L-selectin, which is maintained on all activated F5/LDeltaP cells (XREF_FIG C), does not improve survival or increase retention of virus specific CD8 + T cells at the site of infection.
